<linker>
  <!-- The TAC world is built entirely from GameObject.CreatePrimitive, which
       attaches Sphere/Capsule/Box colliders (we destroy them immediately, but
       the classes must exist for the call to succeed). The code-only scene
       references no collider assets except the ShaderRef cube's BoxCollider,
       so iOS IL2CPP stripping removed the physics module — every Sphere()/Cyl()
       on device logged "Can't add component because class 'SphereCollider'
       doesn't exist!". Preserve the whole physics module (same class of fix as
       the ShaderRef shader pinning). -->
  <assembly fullname="UnityEngine.PhysicsModule" preserve="all"/>
</linker>
